{
  "doc_id": "4561",
  "text": "Real-time quantitative PCR (qPCR) analyses of the frog swabs were used to test for Bd infection, prevalence and intensity. Swabs were analyzed at San Francisco State University (San Francisco, California, United States), using the protocol described by [CITATION_1] with the following changes: swab extracts were analyzed singly instead of in triplicate since use of singletons and triplicates has been found to give similar results in previous studies [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . In addition, BSA was added to the qPCR master mix (1 µL BSA per reaction) [CITATION_4] .",
